<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Critical Error Alert</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333333;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: #ffffff;
        border-radius: 5px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }
      .header {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #eeeeee;
        background-color: #f8d7da;
        color: #721c24;
      }
      .content {
        padding: 20px 0;
      }
      .error-box {
        background-color: #f8f9fa;
        border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
        padding: 15px;
        margin: 20px 0;
        font-family: monospace;
        font-size: 14px;
        overflow-x: auto;
      }
      .footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px 0;
        color: #777777;
        font-size: 14px;
        border-top: 1px solid #eeeeee;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h1>ðŸš¨ Critical Error Alert</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h2>Critical Error in {{appName}}</h2>
        <p>A critical error has occurred in the application at <strong>{{timestamp}}</strong>.</p>
        <p><strong>Error Details:</strong></p>
        <div class="error-box">
          {{errorMessage}}
        </div>
        <p>Please investigate this issue immediately.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2025 {{appName}}. All rights reserved.</p>
        <p>This is an automated alert. Please do not reply to this email.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>